<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-reporting-highlights">Reporting Highlights</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Lopsided Contracts: </strong>Experts say World Cup contracts lock host cities out of prospective revenues more than ever, leaving FIFA with a larger share of the revenue.</li>



<li><strong>Texans on the Hook: </strong>A Texas taxpayer-funded program helps cover costs, but the state struggles to calculate whether there is a benefit.</li>



<li><strong>Lacking Transparency: </strong>Many cities have fought the release of their contracts with FIFA. Those that are public have key cost and revenue information redacted.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-propublica-reporting-highlights__disclaimer">These highlights were written by the reporters and editors who worked on this story.</p>

</div>


